# CampusOps — Distributed Cloud-Native Backend

A professional, production-grade backend for the CampusOps campus management platform. Designed as a **distributed, cloud-ready** application to align with your Distributed Applications and Cloud Computing courses.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Technology Stack Decisions** — I'm recommending the following stack based on what's best for a professional, distributed, secure web application. Please confirm:
> 1. **Runtime**: Node.js 20+ with **TypeScript** (strong typing, better security, industry standard)
> 2. **Framework**: **Express.js** (simple, battle-tested, huge ecosystem)
> 3. **Database**: **PostgreSQL** (best for relational data, free cloud hosting on Supabase/Neon/Railway)
> 4. **ORM**: **Prisma** (type-safe, auto-generated types, visual studio, easy migrations)
> 5. **Cache/Queue**: **Redis** (session store, rate limiting, pub/sub for real-time notifications)
> 6. **Containerization**: **Docker + Docker Compose** (essential for distributed apps course)

> [!WARNING]
> The project structure is designed as a **microservice-ready monolith** — meaning it's modular enough to be split into independent services later (for your distributed apps course demo), but starts as a single deployable unit to avoid premature complexity.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Cloud Deployment** — The architecture supports deployment to any cloud provider (AWS, GCP, Azure, Railway, Render). We'll containerize everything so you can demonstrate cloud computing concepts like:
> - Container orchestration (Docker Compose / Kubernetes)
> - Horizontal scaling of API instances
> - Managed database services
> - Environment-based configuration
> - Health checks and monitoring

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Client Layer"
        FE["🌐 Frontend (Landing + Dashboard)"]
        TG["🤖 Telegram Bot"]
        WA["📱 WhatsApp (Optional)"]
    end

    subgraph "API Gateway Layer"
        NGINX["🔀 Nginx / Load Balancer"]
    end

    subgraph "Application Layer (Docker Containers)"
        API["⚡ Express API Server"]
        WORKER["⏰ Background Worker (Cron Jobs)"]
        BOT["🤖 Telegram Bot Service"]
    end

    subgraph "Data Layer"
        PG["🐘 PostgreSQL"]
        REDIS["🔴 Redis (Cache + Queue)"]
    end

    subgraph "External Services"
        MAIL["📧 IMAP/SMTP Email"]
        TGAPI["📡 Telegram API"]
        OCLAW["🦞 OpenClaw Orchestrator"]
    end

    FE --> NGINX
    TG --> TGAPI
    NGINX --> API
    API --> PG
    API --> REDIS
    WORKER --> PG
    WORKER --> REDIS
    WORKER --> MAIL
    WORKER --> TGAPI
    WORKER --> OCLAW
    BOT --> TGAPI
    BOT --> API
```

